      <authorname>Amarinda</authorname>
      <text>I'll try to be as brief as possible. Riiight. *sagenod*
I'm in the process of making changes to guild administration. All guilds,
both large and small, are being worked with. Here's the game plan:

The guilds are divided up into six different groupings. Each group can be
seen as the opposite of another. I am working with Female Canneling and
Male Channeling, Home Lands and Foreign Lands, then Non-National Armies
and the Shadow. Now.. the reason this can be done and the most important
part of this.

The immortal GLs, as you have seen, are sporting new titles and most all
have the &quot;IMMORTAL&quot; pretitle. This is because they are no longer what we
have considered 'GLs'. They have become Group Leaders. A Group Leader is
an immortal that handles a specific aspect of the guilds (see groups that
I listed). They are responsible for supervising their area and performing
imm tasks that the guild needs. They are also the guys with disguise and
echo that bring you quests. They are going to be out and about and taking
an active interest in their area, be it doing things that have long been
needing done, say within the small guilds, or asking you about plots or
plans. What happened to the Guild Leader position, though?

Guild Leaders are now entirely mortal positions. We've always had our
Mort GLs or MGLs, but they've never been the actual leader except where
the imm position was vacant. Well, things change, and now they are. In
most policies and procedures and IC lives, the immortal will have the
final say but I will no longer be hiring an immortal to lead one guild.

There is one exception to this and that is Shadow. Within the Shadow and
considering the unique way that it runs, a Mort GL will not be hired. We
have Shai'tan and who wants to face that?

So, I'm going to be putting in a helpfile tonight on what I want in an
application. Before the helpfile (I will post once it's complete) look
at the previous posts by myself and Hartigan. We need Morts to GL all
the guilds. I will also be updating wizlist tonight so that you can see
who is running what department without me listing here. I do ask that
you be patient with us as this new system will have bugs, like any other.

Was that short and sweet? Hmm. Tackle me with questions. :)
</text>
