      <text>For those of you curious about the recent sitebannings, the reasons were
fairly simple. After ranting and raving and trying to get someone else
sitebanned for personality conflicts that arose on an entirely different
MUD, one of the persons being subjected to the hateful treatment mailed
the bannees and told them to grow up and leave him alone. When they tried
to use this mail as proof that he was harassing them, the Admin staff had
enough of them. Their GL was even talking about quitting because of the
constant stress she was under from them.

The bottom line is that if you hate someone from Reflections of the Wheel
or Tales of the Ta'veren or The Creator's Shadow or where ever, leave it
there. Trying to get us to punish a player because of bad relations you
have with them elsewhere is likely to backfire on you. If they truly
are just Satan incarnate, give them enough rope and they'll do something
we can punish them for. Or even better, expend your efforts bitching
at the admin on the place where the conflict arose. You'll have a better
chance of succeeding.

-Tze
</text>
