responsibility to assist all of you with your roleplaying experiences.
Yay!
I've got pom-pom's and everything!
Seriously, if you decide you'd like to run an IC event of your own, the
steps to follow are outlined in &amp;rhelp quests&amp;n. Again, I encourage you
to read that. It's my job to keep you happy, but it's your job to keep me
busy! Flood my mailbox with requests. Make me work for that pretitle!
Also, not -all- of the quests I do will be IC RP quests. Gotta show some
love for that OOC stuff as well, right? And since I'm new to this position
suggestions are most welcome. Suggestions for the -type- of quests, I mean,
not as to how many times a day a quest should be run, or what time of day
is best for you to beg me to run a quest. Not that I expect any of you to
do either of those things. I know full well that you all know better.
Ahem.
Now then, my job, really, is to make this place even more fun and exciting
than it already is. I can't do that by myself. I can certainly try, but
the result will probably not be what either of us was hoping for. Those
of you who know me in my other forms know that I will always listen to
what you have to say. Tell me what you think about what I'm doing, or, in 
some cases, what I'm -not- doing. Questions, comments, suggestions, even
complaints - all are welcome. The more comfortable I feel in my new position,
the more quests and different types of quests I'll be able to run. But if my
first quest sucks, and nobody tells me, all the rest are going to suck, too.
Keep that in mind. Constructive criticism is a good thing.
Deanna.
