Nobility levels and that's great.  But with all the rulers, we need
rulees!  So this is what I'm going to do to try and encourage people to
play servants, guards and other positions within the Nations guild that
does not include a Lord or Lady rank.  Number one, I'm raising the amount
of sponsors needed for a Noble character from two to four.  With all the
new guys and old guys we have around, I really don't see this as being a
problem.  I'll even offer to be one of the sponsors if people ask me for
some roleplay.  Number two, I'm going to offer five questpoints right off
for anyone that makes a character within nations other than a noble as
well offer to award them an additional two qps, on top of the five they
would already get, for any roleplay logs that I receive.  So think up some
interesting character concepts, get with some of the Nobles and see if any
of them would be willing to have a maid, a butler, guard or perhaps even
part-time seamstress.  The number of ideas that someone can come up with
are really limitless and you're not constricted by the rules that usually
govern a noble's behavior.    
